### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change.

+*  In the Windows Consumption plan, use app setting named `languageWorkers:java:arguments`.

### Issue describing the changes in this PR

add logic to handle break change when customer using old java library and maven plugin where worker using restructured library. On old plugin the java library jar will not be put in customer lib folder. Worker now only depends on core library so it means worker cannot get annotation class from customer code. Add logics to handle this and avoid the break change. 

### Pull request checklist

Release notes

Sourced from h2's releases.

Version 2.1.210

Two security vulnerabilities in H2 Console (CVE-2022-23221 and possible DNS rebinding attack) are fixed.

Persistent databases created by H2 2.0.x don't need to be upgraded. Persistent databases created by H2 1.4.200 and older versions require export into SQL script with that old version and creation of a new database with the new version and execution of this script in it.
